The paper discusses machine reading comprehension (MRC) models and proposes a new method for reframing MRC datasets as interactive, partially observable environments. This involves adding context-sensitive commands that reveal hidden text to a model, which can then seek relevant information through sequential decision making. This work involves natural language processing (NLP), artificial intelligence (AI), information retrieval (IR), and human-computer interaction (HCI), which are all relevant to the computer science sub-categories of "cs.CL" (Computation and Language), "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence), "cs.IR" (Information Retrieval), "cs.LG" (Machine Learning), and "cs.HC" (Human-Computer Interaction).
